data.chText: 顶峰；高峰
data.enText: the point when sb/sth is best, most successful, strongest, etc.

data.chText: 上午8、9点钟之间是交通高峰期。
data.enText: Traffic reaches its peak between 8 and 9 in the morning.

data.chText: 她正处在事业的巅峰。
data.enText: She's at the peak of her career.

data.chText: 婚后生活的起起伏伏
data.enText: the peaks and troughs of married life

data.chText: 山峰；峰峦
data.enText: the pointed top of a mountain; a mountain with a pointed top

data.chText: 山峰
data.enText: a mountain peak

data.chText: 积雪覆盖的 / 嶙峋怪异的群峰
data.enText: snow-capped/jagged peaks

data.chText: 登山者在半山腰设置营地。
data.enText: The climbers made camp halfway up the peak.

data.chText: 尖形；尖端；尖头
data.enText: any narrow and pointed shape, edge, etc.

data.chText: 把蛋清搅成硬尖状。
data.enText: Whisk the egg whites into stiff peaks.
bill
visor

data.chText: 帽舌；帽檐
data.enText: the stiff front part of a cap that sticks out above your eyes

data.chText: 达到高峰；达到最高值
data.enText: to reach the highest point or value

data.chText: 20世纪80年代初期，石油产量达到了最高峰。
data.enText: Oil production peaked in the early 1980s.

data.chText: 失业率达到17%的最高点。
data.enText: Unemployment peaked at 17%.

data.chText: 一位恰在最佳时刻缔造出最佳成绩的运动员
data.enText: an athlete who peaks (= produces his or her best performance) at just the right time

data.chText: 最高度的；高峰时期的；巅峰状态的
data.enText: used to describe the highest level of sth, or a time when the greatest number of people are doing sth or using sth

data.chText: 那是对该产品需求最旺的时期。
data.enText: It was a time of peak demand for the product.

data.chText: 三月是我们公司业务最繁忙的时期之一。
data.enText: March is one of the peak periods for our business.

data.chText: 所有运动员都处在巅峰状态。
data.enText: The athletes are all in peak condition .

data.chText: 我们在最繁忙的季节需要额外人手。
data.enText: We need extra help during the peak season .

ex.chText: 从那间屋子的阳台上能够看到终年被积雪覆盖的山峰。
ex.enText: You can see peaks covered with snow all the year round from the balcony of that room.

ex.chText: 那名运动员并未处在巅峰状态。
ex.enText: That athlete wasn't at his peak.

ex.chText: 上个月销售额创了新高。
ex.enText: Sales reached a new peak last month.

synonyms.bx: 指山的尖顶；也指人或事物最成功或状态最好的时期。

ex.enText: reach the summit of Mount Qomolangma

ex.chText: 哪项发明能够代表科学成就的顶峰？
ex.enText: What invention can represent the summit of scientific achievement?

synonyms.bx: 指山的最高部分，也可喻指某事物的最大数量或最高水平。

ex.chText: 那座山的山顶覆盖着白雪。
ex.enText: The top of that mountain is covered with snow.

ex.chText: 把这个碗放在冰箱上面。
ex.enText: Place the bowl on the top of the fridge.

ex.chText: 把身份证号码写在页面上端。
ex.enText: Write your ID card number on the top of the page.

ex.chText: 他成功地一步步升到了最高层。
ex.enText: He managed to work his way up to the top.

synonyms.bx: 泛指某物的最上端；也指机构、公司、行业等中的最高职位。

tr: a brim that projects to the front to shade the eyes
example: he pulled down the bill of his cap and trudged ahead

tr: the top or extreme point of something (usually a mountain or hill)
example: the view from the peak was magnificent
they clambered to the tip of Monadnock
the region is a few molecules wide at the summit
at the peak of the pyramid

tr: the most extreme possible amount or value

example: the cannibal's teeth were filed to sharp points

tr: the highest level or degree attainable
example: his landscapes were deemed the acme of beauty
the artist's gifts are at their acme
at the height of her career
...catapulted Einstein to the pinnacle of fame
so many highest superlatives achieved by man
at the top of his profession

tr: the period of greatest prosperity or productivity
Bids for the painting topped out at $50 million"
example: That wild, speculative spirit peaked in 1929

value.def: The peak of a process or an activity is the point at which it is at its strongest, most successful, or most fully developed.

example.ex: The party's membership has fallen from a peak of fifty-thousand after the Second World War...
example.tran: 二战后该党党员人数已从5万人的峰值下降了。

example.ex: The bomb went off in a concrete dustbin at the peak of the morning rush hour.
example.tran: 在最繁忙的交通早高峰期，那枚炸弹在一个混凝土垃圾箱里爆炸了。

example.ex: ...a flourishing career that was at its peak at the time of his death...
example.tran: 他去世时正处于巅峰的欣欣向荣的事业

value.def: When something peaks, it reaches its highest value or its highest level.

example.ex: Temperatures have peaked at over thirty degrees Celsius...
example.tran: 温度最高达30摄氏度以上。
那场危机在1974年7月达到巅峰。
他的事业在20世纪70年代达到顶峰。

value.tran: 达到顶点；达到顶峰；达到最高值

value.def: The peak level or value of something is its highest level or value.

example.ex: Calls cost 36p (cheap rate) and 48p (peak rate) per minute...
example.tran: 电话每分钟36便士（优惠费率）和48便士（高峰费率）。

example.ex: We bought it at the wrong time and paid the peak price.
example.tran: 我们买的时机不合适，买了个最高价。

value.def: Peak times are the times when there is most demand for something or most use of something.

example.ex: It's always crowded at peak times...
During peak periods, reservations are difficult to make at some of the hotels.
example.tran: 在高峰时期，有些酒店很难预订到房间。

value.def: A peak is a mountain or the top of a mountain.
The peak of a cap is the part at the front that sticks out above your eyes.

example.ex: The man touched the peak of his cap.
example.tran: 那名男子摸了摸他的帽舌。
